## Information Exchange Interaction Description
The Push (Unsolicited Communication) information exchange interaction is a alternative way to handle a Push interation for a FHIR APIs. It uses the Communication Resource to express the information associated with the unsolicited delivery of information through a FHIR API. A system acting as the Information Sender delivers a communication message to a system acting as an Information Recipient  using the FHIR API available for the Information Recipient.  The interaction results in a message and a payload of information being delivered to the Information Recipient. The recipient system's business rules for processing the communicated information are outside the scope of this implementation guide.
